description: India's "Swasth Nari, Sashakt Parivar Abhiyaan" campaign has achieved a global recognition, securing three Guinness World Records. The initiative, focused on women-led health empowerment and nutrition, saw millions register for healthcare platforms and screenings. Union Health Minister JP Nadda hailed the milestone as progress towards a healthier and empowered India.
title: India sets 3 Guinness World Records; JP Nadda shares details of health campaign

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: Kerala Chief Minister Pinarayi Vijayan announced the state is free of extreme poverty. The opposition United Democratic Front rejected the claim as fraud. They boycotted the assembly session in protest. The Chief Minister responded that their actions reflect their own behavior. He stated the government implements what it says.
title: Kerala becomes 1st state to eradicate 'extreme poverty', says CM in assembly

author: ALOKKNMISHRA
description: Tejashwi Yadav, INDIA bloc's Bihar CM candidate, pledges to transform the state into a job creation hub, ending migration. He highlights plans for factories, educational institutions, and healthcare, contrasting them with the NDA's perceived lack of vision for Bihar. Yadav dismisses 'jungle raj' fears, emphasizing economic justice and inclusive development.
title: 'My age may be young, but ... ': Tejashwi shares how he plans to fulfill govt job promise; slams NDA

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: America faces its longest federal government shutdown. Economists warn this impasse is hurting the economy. Millions of federal workers are not getting paid. Small businesses are at risk of losing billions. Healthcare and early education programs are also impacted. The economic damage is mounting daily. This situation is creating significant hardship for many Americans.
title: Over $7 billion wiped out! How US govt shutdown is hitting the American economy

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: Delhi BJP MP Praveen Khandelwal has urged Home Minister Amit Shah to rename the national capital 'Indraprastha,' citing its ancient heritage linked to the Pandavas.
title: 'Rename Delhi to Indraprastha': BJP MP writes to HM; calls for installing Pandavas statues

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Shreyas Iyer has been discharged from a Sydney hospital after suffering a ruptured spleen and rib cage injury during a match against Australia. He sustained the injury while attempting a catch, leading to ICU treatment. Iyer is now recovering in Sydney and will return to India when medically cleared.
title: Shreyas Iyer: BCCI provides positive update on injury; shares roadmap

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: "For decades, our foreign policy has been trapped in a counterproductive and endless cycle of regime change or nation building,' said Gabbard. "It was a one-size-fits-all approach, of toppling regimes, trying to impose our system of governance on others, intervene in conflicts that were barely understood and walk away with more enemies than allies."
title: Tulsi Gabbard says regime change era over; but stays quiet on Venezuela

author: TNN
description: A Lucknow police sub-inspector has found himself in deep trouble after being caught in the act, taking a Rs 2 lakh bribe for a biased report regarding a gang rape incident. The entire transaction was recorded in a viral video—a key element of a sting operation by the Anti-Corruption Organisation.
title: Watch: UP cop nabbed taking Rs 2 lakh bribe to drop name of rape accused; video viral

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: BlackRock's private credit arm, HPS Investment Partners, alleges a multi-million-dollar fraud by Bankim Brahmbhatt's telecom firms. Lenders claim Brahmbhatt fabricated receivables used as collateral for over $500 million in loans. Brahmbhatt's companies have filed for bankruptcy, and he is reportedly in India.
title: Who is Bankim Brahmbhatt? Indian-origin CEO accused of $500m scam at BlackRock

author: V NARAYAN
description: A chilling hostage drama unfolded in Mumbai when a web series shoot turned real. Children, believing they were filming a scene, were held captive for hours by the director, Rohit Aarrya, who threatened them with a gun and rod. Prepared with flammable materials, Aarrya's plan was revealed after he pulled out weapons, leading to a tense standoff and eventual rescue.
title: Mumbai hostage scare: Kids gagged, hands tied for hrs for 'scene’ shoot; witnesses recount horror

author: SEHJAL GUPTA
description: The horse racing community mourns jockey Tommie Jakes, 19, found dead at home. Jakes was a rising star, riding for top trainer George Boughey. He achieved his first win at 16. His sudden passing has sent shockwaves through the sport. Tributes pour in from jockeys and trainers. Police confirmed the death is not suspicious. A coroner's inquiry is underway.
title: Jockey Tommie Jakes, 19, dies hours after final ride as racing world mourns

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Bihar chief minister Nitish Kumar released a video message urging voters to support NDA candidates in the upcoming assembly elections. He highlighted his government's development work since 2005, contrasting it with the previous regime and criticising dynastic politics. Kumar emphasised his commitment to serving all sections of society and pledged further development for Bihar.
title: 'Did nothing for own family': Nitish's video message for voters; takes veiled dig at Lalu

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Indian opener Abhimanyu Easwaran finds Gautam Gambhir's coaching beneficial. Gambhir, a former successful opening batter, shares valuable insights. Easwaran has learned much from their discussions on batting. They focus on practicing techniques suited to different surfaces. Gambhir's guidance is impacting Easwaran's game positively. India are currently playing a T20I series in Australia.
title: Dropped from India squad! Easwaran makes fresh Gambhir admission: 'Just like me'

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Abhishek Sharma admitted Australia's bowlers surprised India with their disciplined execution in Melbourne. Despite scoring 68, India lost. Sharma highlighted the difficulty of the wicket and the need to adapt plans when early wickets fell. He praised his partnership with Harshit Rana and the team management's support for his aggressive style.
title: IND vs AUS: Why Gambhir sent Rana ahead of Dube — Abhishek finally reveals

author: TRISHA TEWARI
description: The National Testing Agency (NTA) has opened registration for JEE Main 2026 Session 1, scheduled between January 21 and 30, 2026. Applications are accepted till November 27, 2025. The exam will be held in 13 languages and cover Physics, Chemistry, and Mathematics, serving as the qualifying test for admissions to NITs, IIITs, CFTIs, and IITs via JEE Advanced.
title: JEE Main 2026: Registration for session 1 begins; direct link here

author: AHMED ALI
description: Assistant Police Inspector Amol Waghmare was forced to shoot an armed kidnapper, Rohit Arryya, who had taken several children hostage in a Powai studio. Arryya doused the premises with petrol and threatened to set it ablaze. Police rescued the children after a tense standoff and Waghmare's decisive action.
title: 'Poured petrol all over': What unfolded during Mumbai’s hostage standoff; FIR reveals sequence of events

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: Microsoft is navigating a major AI shift, with CEO Satya Nadella stressing the need to earn trust daily. The company achieved record revenues of $281.7 billion. Microsoft is investing heavily in AI security and quality, expanding its global datacenter presence. Initiatives like Microsoft 365 Copilot and GitHub Copilot are seeing massive user growth. A significant $4 billion investment is planned for AI education and skills development over five years, aiming to empower millions.
title: Satya Nadella's message to employees: Permission not guaranteed always, so earn trust

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: Months after settling a $16 million lawsuit with CBS News, Donald Trump is set to appear on "60 Minutes" this Sunday. Norah O'Donnell conducted the interview at Mar-a-Lago, marking his first appearance since the settlement and signaling improved relations with the broadcaster.
title: Trump returns for a CBS's 60 Minutes after $16 mn settlement; all you need to know

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: The ongoing US government shutdown is severely impacting air travel, with widespread delays and staffing shortages plaguing air traffic control. Many controllers, now missing paychecks, are absent, leading to significant disruptions at major airports. Officials warn of worsening chaos, especially with the Thanksgiving holiday approaching, urging Congress to end the impasse.
title: US govt shutdown: Air traffic controllers unpaid, flights delayed; staffing crunch hits key airports

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: A viral AI-generated video depicting a glowing football stadium atop a skyscraper, mistakenly linked to Saudi Arabia's 2034 FIFA World Cup plans, has garnered millions of views. The creator confirmed it was an imaginative concept, unrelated to any official Saudi projects, despite the kingdom's significant infrastructure investments for the event.
title: Who was behind the 'Sky Stadium' video that went viral on social media?

author: VIJENDER KUMAR
description: A Haryana youth, Yuvraj, was shot dead in Guatemala by smugglers after being held captive while attempting to enter the US via the illegal 'dunki' route. His family paid Rs 25 lakh in advance for the journey, but later received videos of him being beaten and threatened, demanding more money for his release.
title: Haryana teen held hostage on ‘dunki’ route to US, killed; family paid Rs 25L to agents

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: President Trump announced the US will resume nuclear testing, citing actions by Russia and China. This decision reverses a long-standing moratorium, raising concerns about environmental hazards and global tensions. Experts question the technical necessity, while allies warn of an arms race.
title: 'If they're going to do it ... ': Trump doubles down on nuclear testing; underground tests on cards?

author: GLOBAL SPORTS DESK
description: Blue Jays catcher Alejandro Kirk's stellar World Series performance is matched by the heartwarming social media buzz surrounding his wife, Sofia Castaneda. A simple emoji comment from Shane Bieber's wife, Kara, on Sofia's post celebrating Kirk's success ignited a viral moment, highlighting the strong camaraderie among the team's families and captivating fans.
title: Shane Bieber’s wife reacts to Sofia Castaneda’s World Series post, sparking buzz

author: TOI NEWS DESK
title: 'Theatre of proxy war': Doval says no 'major' terror attack in India except in J&K

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Former Australia captain Aaron Finch urged India to reinstate Arshdeep Singh, criticising their batting-heavy lineup for a lack of balance and bowling penetration. Finch believes too many batters can dilute responsibility, and Team India needs the right combinations for the World Cup. He also noted that India's bowlers defended an insufficient total.
title: 'Too many batters, not enough balance' - Ex-Oz captain questions India's strategy

author: GAURAV GUPTA
description: Jemimah Rodrigues delivered a match-winning unbeaten 127 against Australia in the 2025 Women's ODI World Cup semifinals, overcoming severe anxiety. She revealed her emotional struggle and the crucial support from teammates, emphasizing the importance of seeking help for mental health challenges. Rodrigues's resilient performance secured India's victory and a place in the finals.
title: Women's WC: Finding calm in chaos - Jemimah opens up on struggle with anxiety

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Ravichandran Ashwin has criticised India's team management for excluding Arshdeep Singh from the playing XI against Australia. Ashwin argued that if experimentation was the goal, Jasprit Bumrah should have been rested instead of Arshdeep, India's leading T20I wicket-taker. He emphasised Arshdeep's consistent performance and asserted his right to a regular spot in the team.
title: IND vs AUS: 'Please, play him!' - Ashwin slams Team India over Arshdeep's exclusion

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Pakistan's Babar Azam has become the leading scorer in men's T20 internationals, surpassing Rohit Sharma. Azam achieved this milestone during Pakistan's dominant nine-wicket victory over South Africa, leveling the series. Youngster Saim Ayub also shone with an unbeaten 71, guiding Pakistan to a swift chase after their bowlers restricted South Africa to 110.
title: On top of the world! Babar Azam breaks Rohit Sharma's big T20 record; PAK crush SA

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Seventeen-year-old Australian cricketer Ben Austin tragically passed away after sustaining fatal injuries during a net session. The incident has sent shockwaves through the cricket community, prompting tributes and renewed discussions on player safety.  The loss has evoked painful memories of Phillip Hughes and led to widespread mourning.
title: 'Ben Austin was only 17 …': Dhawan pens heartfelt message; cricket mourns tragic loss

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Berlin Brandenburg Airport experienced flight suspensions for nearly two hours due to unidentified drone sightings, a recurring issue across Europe.  Take-offs and landings were halted, leading to flight diversions, as police investigated the drone incursions. This incident highlights a growing "hybrid threat" concern for Germany and other European nations.
title: Berlin airport briefly halts flights after unidentified drone sightings

author: JAI NARAIN PANDEY
description: The NDA unveiled its Bihar election manifesto, promising over one crore employment opportunities through skill development and infrastructure projects. The alliance also focused on welfare schemes, including financial aid for women and EBC youth, and pledged to top up PM-KISAN support with an additional annual payout.
title: Bihar polls: NDA promises 1 cr jobs, infra push; plans new cities, airports in state vision

author: SHUBHANSHU DWIVEDI
description: Parvez Rasool, the first cricketer from Jammu and Kashmir to represent India, reflects on his impactful career and looks back on his retirement. He highlights the significant progress in J&K cricket, attributing it to opening doors for aspiring players. Rasool also discusses the challenges faced by domestic performers from smaller states and the overshadowing effect of IPL performances over consistent domestic achievements.
title: Exclusive - 'Didn't get enough chances': Parvez Rasool questions the system

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: IPL Chairman Arun Dhumal lauded India's bench strength and the enduring class of Rohit Sharma and Virat Kohli. Dhumal highlighted Rohit's Player of the Series performance against Australia, showcasing his conviction and work ethic, and expressed confidence in their continued contributions to Indian cricket.
title: 'Knocking at the door': Suryavanshi set for India call-up? IPL chief hails bench strength

author: VISHWA MOHAN
description: November nights are predicted to be warmer than usual across most of India, with the exception of some northwest regions. Day temperatures are expected to be normal to below normal, contributing to a pleasant month nationwide. October saw significantly higher rainfall than average, marking it as the second wettest since 2001.
title: November likely to be quite pleasant in large parts of India: IMD

title: Powai hostage crisis: Kids gagged, hands tied for hours for film shoot

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: Effective November 1, 2025, Aadhaar updates for name, address, and mobile number can be initiated online via the myAadhaar portal, eliminating the need for in-person visits for many demographic changes. Biometric updates still require a visit to an Aadhaar Seva Kendra. The UIDAI has also revised fee structures and emphasized timely PAN-Aadhaar linkage.
title: UIDAI announces change in Aadhaar rules from November 1; here's what has changed

author: TOI WORLD DESK
title: 'Breathtaking fraud': BlackRock accuses Indian-origin CEO of $500m scam — All you need to know

author: NIKITA PATNAIK
description: Taylor Swift set the tone for fall 2025 in New York City with an elegant monochrome brown ensemble. The pop megastar's sophisticated look, featuring a turtleneck sweater dress and suede boots, embraced autumn's cozy palette. She also proudly displayed her engagement ring from Travis Kelce, proving her impeccable style continues to command attention.
title: Taylor Swift steps out in chic brown look, shows off Travis Kelce engagement ring

author: ALOKKNMISHRA
description: Tejashwi Prasad Yadav, INDIA bloc's CM candidate, vows to make Bihar number one by focusing on employment, education, healthcare and industrial growth. He dismissed 'jungle raj' claims as propaganda and asserted the RJD's inclusive support base, aiming to end migration for work and studies.
title: Tejashwi Yadav vows to make Bihar India’s number one state
